      143:"Despite the tragedies, we do not give up on smiling",
      144:" the most gracious, the most merciful Praise be to God, by whose grace good deeds are accomplished. Praise be to God, who has enabled us and guided us to do good. Praise be to God, who has honored us and helped us and made our deeds easy for us. Praise be to God, who has made us a means and help in delivering goodness to those who deserve it from the weak and needy, who do not ask people urgently. Praise be to God, who has crowned our efforts and made us see the fruit of our deeds. May peace and blessings be upon our master Muhammad, his good and pure family, and his chosen and good companions",
      145:" Since the launch of the blessed Banan Charitable and Developmental Foundation, and with the grace of God Almighty - and the combined efforts of sincere and charitable people - the Foundation has been able to achieve great successes in the fields of charitable work, as those in charge of it realize their responsibility towards those who are in dire need of extending a helping hand and assistance to them. The Foundation’s work is only a form of social solidarity that our true religion urges us to achieve by carrying out its duty to alleviate the suffering of the poor, needy, and orphans of dear Yemen. Based on the principle of cooperation in righteousness and piety, and in implementation of the Almighty’s saying (They ask you, “What should they spend?” Say, “Whatever good you spend, it is for the parents, and the relatives, and the orphans, and the needy, and the wayfarer.” Do not do any good, for God is All-Knowing of it.” (Al-Baqarah 215) By providing a comprehensive database on those in need, followed by preparing diverse and integrated programs that take care of the beneficiary to achieve the desired goals. Hence, I take this opportunity and extend my sincere thanks and praise to the generous people for their continued support of the Foundation and its charitable works, appreciating their dedication, sincerity and constant support in order to achieve the lofty mission adopted by the Foundation. Thanks are extended to all members of the Foundation and employees for their blessed and fruitful efforts. We ask all individuals, entities, private and public institutions, and business and financial men to cooperate with us in order to achieve our humanitarian mission and to contribute as much as possible to helping the needy in various fields, especially developmental, educational and other projects that would contribute to building the individual and society. May God’s blessings and peace be upon our Master Muhammad, his pure family, and his chosen companions",
